{
  "texts": [
    "We find that initialising ClinicalDistilBERT with the trained weights from a pre-existing biomedical model significantly improved the model's average performance, particularly on the MedNLI dataset.",
    "However, we discovered that initialising the ClinicalMobileBERT with a similar biomedical checkpoint did not result in a significant performance boost.",
    "Latency and Giga Multiply-Accumulate Operations per second (GMACs) are two important metrics used to evaluate the efficiency of machine learning models.",
    "Latency measures the amount of time it takes for a model to process a single input and produce an output and is typically measured in milliseconds.",
    "Cs, on the other hand, stands for Giga Multiply-Accumulate Operations and is a measure of how many computational operations a model needs to perform its tasks."
  ]
}